<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="558" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="74.[790,1384,1344,1767]" lastBlockId="74.[171,1385,1773,3464]" pageId="74" pageNumber="558">
<taxonomicName box="[796,1113,1498,1531]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Uroderma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="558" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magnirostrum">Uroderma magnirostrum</taxonomicName>
was described 50 years ago after a review of the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Uroderma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="558" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Uroderma</taxonomicName>
yielded unmistakable results that there was an unrecognized species embedded in previously collected specimens of the much more common 
<taxonomicName box="[1211,1376,1698,1727]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Uroderma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="558" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilobatum">U. bilobatum</taxonomicName>
, with which it overlaps in much ofits distribution. Because of the original description, its taxonomy has remained stable. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
